A special official provincial funeral for business tycoon Dr. Thandi Ndlovu takes place at the House of Treasure Ministries south of Johannesburg on Friday morning. Ndlovu who was a medical doctor by profession died in a car crash in Rustenburg on Saturday. She’s been hailed for venturing into the male-dominated construction industry when she founded Motheo Construction and for her role in the struggle as a member of the ANC’s former armed wing uMkhonto we Sizwe.  Ndlovu is known as a fearless business leader, social activist and champion for women empowerment. Her impact was felt in her professional and personal space. Click on the videos below:   